value.description:
Currently the Cosmos Hub, valued at over $1.5B, enforces a 0.01% slashing penalty for validators down for 9500 consecutive blocks (~19 hours).

If passed, this governance proposal will decrease the downtime slashing penalty for Microtick validators from 1% to 0.1% (ie. 10x the penalty of the Cosmos Hub). Assuming a 6s block time, Microtick validators that are offline for approximately 9 consecutive hours will be slashed 0.1%.
value.title: Reduce the validator downtime slashing penalty from 1% to 0.1%

value.description:
This is a proposal to upgrade from microtickzone-a1 to microtickzone-a2 to fix some issues, to add several markets, and to free up disk space for operators. Instructions for the upgrade can be found here: https://github.com/microtick/validator/blob/upgrade-1/README.md

If this proposal passes, validators should:

1. Halt the chain and export the state at Block Height 3416000.
2. Use v1.0.1 of the Microtick software, verifying that the commit hash is 13c5059c68a7322fa6da41d6031ebc8d3f9f575b

Genesis will begin as soon as 66.67% of consensus voting power is online. We recommend that operators attend the Microtick community Discord server to verify the hash of the genesis file before launching: https://discord.gg/jz7Jt95

We are targeting March 23, 15:00 UTC for the upgrade, but the precise time will vary due to variances in block times. The chain halt will therefore take place when the block height  3,416,000 is reached. Operators may find the v1.0.1 binaries here: https://microtick.com/releases/mainnet/

In the event of a failure to launch, we will not restart microtickzone-a1. The Microtick team and community will coordinate off-chain to launch microtickzone-a2 with the minimum possible software and genesis file changes.

List of changes:
1. Fix the staking amounts for slashed delegations.
2. Add a security patch.
3. Update to the genesis file to add new markets and revert one invalid transaction. No parameter or account changes.
4. Clear the state (less disk space).
value.title: Microtick microtickzone-a2 upgrade
